166|[[Pallacanestro Virtus Roma|Calze Pompea Roma]]|ITA|79\u201380|79\u201386|winner=2}}\n|}\n\n==Semi finals==\n{{TwoLeg start}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[KK Crvena zvezda|Crvena zvezda]]|FRY|155\u2013145|[[Cholet Basket|Cholet]]|FRA|81\u201349|74\u201396|winner=1}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[Scaligera Basket Verona|Riello Mash Verona]]|ITA|166\u2013154|[[Pallacanestro Virtus Roma|Calze Pompea Roma]]|ITA|96\u201382|70\u201372|winner=1}}\n|}\n\n==Finals==\n{{TwoLeg start}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[Scaligera Basket Verona|Riello Mash Verona]]|ITA|141\u2013138|[[KK Crvena zvezda|Crvena zvezda]]|FRY|68\u201374|73\u201364|winner=1}}\n|}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center; margin:auto\"\n!1997\u201398 FIBA Kora\u0107 Cup Champions\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ITA|size=100px}}<br /> '''[[Scaligera Basket Verona|Riello Mash Verona]]''' <br /> '''1st title'''\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[1997\u201398 FIBA EuroLeague]]\n* [[1997\u201398 FIBA EuroCup]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Scaligera Basket Verona 1997\u201398 FIBA Kora\u0107 Cup Winners}}\n{{Kora\u0107 Cup seasons}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Korac Cup}}\n[[Category:FIBA Kora\u0107 Cup|1997-98]]\n[[Category:1997\u201398 in European basketball]]\n", "name_user": "GoingBatty", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 -WP:WCWproject (Double pipe in a link - Include tag error)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1997%E2%80%9398_FIBA_Kora%C4%87_Cup"}
{"title_page": "Gostaham", "text_new": "[[File:Gustaham_(The_Shahnama_of_Shah_Tahmasp).png|thumb|right|In the [[Shahnameh of Shah Tahmasp]].]]\n'''Gostaham'''<ref name=\"iranica\">{{cite web|last1=Djalal Khaleghi-Motlagh|first1=Djalal|title=GOSTAHAM|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/gostaham|publisher=ENCYCLOP\u00c6DIA IRANICA|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> ({{lang-fa|\u06af\u064f\u0633\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0645}}) is the name of a number of Iranian heroes in [[Shahnameh]].\n\n== Son of Nowzar ==\nThe first Gostaham is the son of [[Nowzar]] and the younger brother of [[Tous son of Nowzar|Tous]]. His name was first mentioned in the reign of his father. He was installed as a local ruler in [[Turan]] by [[Kay Khosrow]]. He is among the heroes who disappeared (or died) in snow during Kay Khosrow's ascent to heaven. Beside Gostaham, four other Iranian heroes also disappeared in this accident. There's a mountain pass named Molla-ye Bi\u017ean in the [[Kohgiluya]] district where as believed by locals, is where the heroes disappeared. He was also mentioned in other sources. The unknown author of Mojmal al-taw\u0101rik\u00f2 wrote what he was called \"r\u0101st-and\u0101z\" (sharpshooter) and \"sa\u1e35t-kam\u0101n var\u0101z\" (sharp-shooting paladin). According to [[Iranica]], he may be that Vistarav son of Naotara (Nowzar) mentioned in [[Avesta]].<ref name=\"iranica\" />\n\n=== Family Tree ===\n\n{{family tree/start}}\n{{family tree | | | | | | MNR | | | | | | |MNR=[[Manuchehr]]}}\n{{family tree | | | | | | |!| |}}\n{{family tree | | | | | | NOZ | | | | | |NOZ=[[Nowzar]]}}\n{{family tree | | | | |,|-|^|-|.| | | | | |}}\n{{family tree | | | | TUS | | GOS | | | |TUS=[[Tous son of Nowzar|Tous]]|GOS='''Gostaham'''}}\n{{family tree/end}}\n\n== Son of Gazhdaham ==\nThe second Gostaham is son of [[Gazhdaham]] and brother of [[Gordafarid]] during the reign of Kay Khosrow. In Shahnameh, he is a friend of [[Bizhan and Manizhe|Bizhan]]. Kay Khosrow does not let him to fight with Turanian heroes in the story of [[Davazdah Rokh]] (Twelve combats). Gostaham is angry of this decision and chase Lahh\u0101k and Far\u0161\u0113d, brothers of [[Piran Viseh]] and kills them. However he himself was severely injured and Bizhan takes him to Kay Khosrow and the latter saves his life by tying a panacean bead around his arm.<ref name=\"iranica\" />\n\nWhen [[Afrasiab]] kills [[Siy\u00e2vash]] in Turan, [[Goudarz]] sends [[Giv (Shahnameh)|Giv]] there to bring Kay Khosrow, Siavash's son, back to Iran. Giv finds Kay Khosrow and his mother, [[Farangis]], after several years. When they arrive at [[Dez-e Sepid]] in the border of Iran and Turan, according to one tradition, Gostaham son of Gazhdaham is the castellan of the fortress.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tafa\u017c\u017col\u012b|first1=A\u1e25mad|title=DE\u017d-E SAF\u012aD|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/dez-e-safid|publisher=ENCYCLOP\u00c6DIA IRANICA|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Shahnameh}}\n\n[[Category:Shahnameh characters]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Gustaham_(The_Shahnama_of_Shah_Tahmasp).png|thumb|right|In the [[Shahnameh of Shah Tahmasp]].]]\n'''Gostaham'''<ref name=\"iranica\">{{cite web|last1=Djalal Khaleghi-Motlagh|first1=Djalal|title=GOSTAHAM|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/gostaham|publisher=ENCYCLOP\u00c6DIA IRANICA|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> ({{lang-fa|\u06af\u064f\u0633\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0645}}) is the name of a number of Iranian heroes in [[Shahnameh]].\n\n== Son of Nowzar ==\nThe first Gostaham is the son of [[Nowzar]] and the younger brother of [[Tous son of Nowzar|Tous]]. His name was first mentioned in the reign of his father. He was installed as a local ruler in [[Turan]] by [[Kay Khosrow]]. He is among the heroes who disappeared (or died) in snow during Kay Khosrow's ascent to heaven. Beside Gostaham, four other Iranian heroes also disappeared in this accident. There's a mountain pass named Molla-ye Bi\u017ean in the [[Kohgiluya]] district where as believed by locals, is where the heroes disappeared. He was also mentioned in other sources. The unknown author of Mojmal al-taw\u0101rik\u00f2 wrote what he was called \"r\u0101st-and\u0101z\" (sharpshooter) and \"sa\u1e35t-kam\u0101n var\u0101z\" (sharp-shooting paladin). According to [[Iranica]], he may be that Vistarav son of Naotara (Nowzar) mentioned in [[Avesta]].<ref name=\"iranica\" />\n\n=== Family Tree ===\n\n{{family tree/start}}\n{{family tree | | | | | | MNR | | | | | | |MNR=[[Manuchehr]]}}\n{{family tree | | | | | | |!| |}}\n{{family tree | | | | | | NOZ | | | | | |NOZ=[[Nowzar]]}}\n{{family tree | | | | |,|-|^|-|.| | | | | |}}\n{{family tree | | | | TUS | | GOS | | | |TUS=[[Tous son of Nowzar|Tous]]|GOS='''Gostaham'''}}\n{{family tree/end}}\n\n== Son of Gazhdaham ==\nThe second Gostaham is son of [[Gazhdaham]] and brother of [[Gordafarid]] during the reign of Kay Khosrow. In Shahnameh, he is a friend of [[Bizhan and Manizhe|Bizhan]]. Kay Khosrow does not let him to fight with Turanian heroes in the story of [[Davazdan Rokh]] (Twelve combats). Gostaham is angry of this decision and chase Lahh\u0101k and Far\u0161\u0113d, brothers of [[Piran Viseh]] and kills them. However he himself was severely injured and Bizhan takes him to Kay Khosrow and the latter saves his life by tying a panacean bead around his arm.<ref name=\"iranica\" />\n\nWhen [[Afrasiab]] kills [[Siy\u00e2vash]] in Turan, [[Goudarz]] sends [[Giv (Shahnameh)|Giv]] there to bring Kay Khosrow, Siavash's son, back to Iran. Giv finds Kay Khosrow and his mother, [[Farangis]], after several years. When they arrive at [[Dez-e Sepid]] in the border of Iran and Turan, according to one tradition, Gostaham son of Gazhdaham is the castellan of the fortress.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tafa\u017c\u017col\u012b|first1=A\u1e25mad|title=DE\u017d-E SAF\u012aD|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/dez-e-safid|publisher=ENCYCLOP\u00c6DIA IRANICA|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Shahnameh}}\n\n[[Category:Shahnameh characters]]\n", "name_user": "Mandarax", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gostaham"}
